snippet: The five members of Me N Ma Girls are battling conservative parents, a censorship board and boyfriends who think it is outrageous that they go onstage in such skimpy outfits.
abstract: Yangon Journal; Myanmar's first girl band Me N Ma Girls battle conservative parents, a censorship board and boyfriends who think it is outrageous that they go onstage in skimpy outfits; as the nation emerges from years of dictatorial military rule and isolation and moves toward the Asian mainstream, government-sanctioned art and dress are being challenged by prospect of more Western-inspired entertainment.
lead_paragraph: The five members of Me N Ma Girls are battling conservative parents, a censorship board and boyfriends who think it is outrageous that they go onstage in such skimpy outfits.

headline.seo: Girl Band Embraces Western Culture, on Burmese Terms
headline.main: Myanmar’s First Girl Band Pushes Limits of Censors, and Parents
headline.print_headline: Myanmar’s First Girl Band Pushes Limits of Censors, and Parents
